- To use propel

1 Time Setup -
- edit runtime-conf.xml and build.properties with the correct database string
- add "source path/to/project/.project-profile" to your .profile or .bash_profile

Using Propel -
- edit schema.xml
	- reference - http://propelorm.org/reference/schema.html

- edit sample data (data.xml)
	- reference - http://propelorm.org/cookbook/working-with-existing-databases.html#dumping_data_to_xml

- enter the propel-orm folder in terminal and issue the following commands

	- propel-gen convert-conf
		- converts the configuration from the xml and build.properties

	- propel-gen om
		- updates the PHP object model classes

	- propel-gen sql
		- generates create table sql scripts

	- propel-gen migrate-sql
		- generates a diff sql script to update the database from schema.xml

	- propel-gen sql-diff
		- diff the current state of schema.xml with the database, generates a sql diff

	- propel-gen migrate
		- executes the migration script generated via diff

	- propel-gen datasql
		- generates data for sql

	- propel-gen datadumb
		- generates a data.xml from the database

	- propel-gen insert-sql
		- inserts the last generated sql command that ran (sql, migrate-sql, data-sql, etc.)

	- propel-gen sql-diff
